"11/30/2018 06:43am","151.35.231.245","0","+393287111695","yari.gregu@icloud.com","06/07/1980","Célibataire","Intendant Général - Régisseur - House manager","1008PA","Dear  Recruiter,
My name is Yari and I wanted to participate in your search for a “ Property manager  “ position  because my professional characteristics reflect your research.

I worked for over 13 years in important hotels and restaurants in Italy and abroad, achieving the status of maitre d'hotel.
I have a lot of practicality at table service, in the kitchen and in the preparation of international meals and drinks.

I am an honest, loyal, respectful and sociable person

I have a lot of practicality in maintenance work, masonry, painting, electrical and hydraulic work.

I am a very dynamic and energetic worker. 

Every day I work at least 12 hours with a lot of passion and dedication

I do not smoke, I do not use drugs or alcohol and I am a family man with a great desire to work peacefully. 

For over 3 years and a half I managed an important and famous villa in Sardinia (Italy) with the role of house manager and butler.
During the winter months I supervised the properties of my employer in London and in the Italian Alps, making sure the house was perfect before the family arrived.

In my career I have always managed a staff getting good results from my collaborators. 
I am used to working in the luxury environment with very demanding guests and accustomed to a high standard of quality.
I kept all aspects of the household running smoothly whilst maintaining a poised and professional demeanor and with very little direction. 
I am passport ready, able to travel, work independently or as part of a team, and use good judgment and care when representing the family.. 
• Clothing and wardrobe management: cleaning, organizing, purchasing, packing, etc.
• Supervise and coordinate with party and catering companies for private events, including the eldest son’s 300 guest wedding. 
• Set up and supervise various appointments and household tasks: cleaning, painting, maintenance, delivery of art and furniture. 
• Coordinate formal and casual table settings for parties, holidays, and family meals. 
• Maintain organization and list of receipts for purchases made, gifts received, etc. 
• Do personal shopping for family including gifts, school supplies, travel needs, wardrobe, etc. 
• Coordinate and work with household staff in regards to the inventory of household supplies, groceries, home maintenance supplies, etc. 
• Complete ad hoc projects as requested. 
• Drive family members to and from different functions, and maintain cars. 
I know the regulations in force concerning hygiene and I have obtained the various professional certificates such as 
HACCP
FIRST AID 
SAFETY ON THE WORKPLACE 
FIRST FIRE FIGHTING INTERVENTION


I hope that you can evaluate my application and I ask you to contact all my previous employers to confirm my professionalism as a house manager butler. 

Kind regerds

Gregu Yari
