I worked for over 13 years in important hotels and restaurants in Italy and abroad, achieving the
status of maitre d'hotel.
I have a lot of practicality at table service, in the kitchen and in the preparation of international
meals and drinks.
For almost 4 years I have managed an important and famous villa in northern Sardinia, in Italy but
has been put up for sale and I would like to look for a new job.
During my experience I also worked with important international businessmen and American actors
I am an honest, loyal, respectful and sociable person, I love traveling, I am a very dynamic and
energetic worker.
Every day I work at least 12 hours with a lot of passion and dedication
I do not smoke, I do not use drugs or alcohol and I am a family man with a great desire to work
peacefully.
I am available to travel and also to live independently in abroad.
During the winter months I supervised the properties of my employer in Sardinia,Milan, London
and in the Italian Alps, making sure the house was perfect before the family arrived.
In my career I have always managed a staff getting good results from my collaborators.
I am used to working in the luxury environment with very demanding guests and accustomed to a
high standard of quality.
I kept all aspects of the household running smoothly whilst maintaining a poised and professional
demeanor and with very little direction.
I am passport ready, able to travel, work independently or as part of a team, and use good
judgment and care when representing the family..
• Clothing and wardrobe management: cleaning, organizing, purchasing, packing, etc.
• Supervise and coordinate with party and catering companies for private events, including the
eldest son’s 300 guest wedding.
• Set up and supervise various appointments and household tasks: cleaning, painting, maintenance,
delivery of art and furniture.
• Coordinate formal and casual table settings for parties, holidays, and family meals.
• Maintain organization and list of receipts for purchases made, gifts received, etc.
• Do personal shopping for family including gifts, school supplies, travel needs, wardrobe, etc.
• Coordinate and work with household staff in regards to the inventory of household supplies,
groceries, home maintenance supplies, etc.
• Complete ad hoc projects as requested.
• Drive family members to and from different functions, and maintain cars.
I know the regulations in force concerning hygiene and I have obtained the various professional
certificates such as
HACCP
FIRST AID
SAFETY ON THE WORKPLACE
FIRST FIRE FIGHTING INTERVENTION
I would like to send written references, and professional certificates. and criminal records
I have the necessary documents to work in the United States
Kind regards
Gregu Yari
